# safety_cot_heads

Unified codebase for the **safety / coherency head ablation** project.
Merges:

* [`ydyjya/SafetyHeadAttribution`](https://github.com/ydyjya/SafetyHeadAttribution) — SHIPS + Sahara attribution.
* [`Lott11/CoT-safety`](https://github.com/Lott11/CoT-safety) — 5-label LLM-as-judge + BeaverTails experiments.

…plus a new **coherency-head** module (NLL / judge-coherence / pathology /
hybrid scoring), a robust JSON-safe judge, sentence-level trajectory analysis,
random/layer-matched controls, OmegaConf configs and deterministic seeds.

> The original code is preserved verbatim under
> [`src/safety_cot_heads/_legacy/`](src/safety_cot_heads/_legacy) and is
> imported from there wherever the original API is sound.  See
> [`docs/MIGRATION.md`](docs/MIGRATION.md) for a file-by-file map.

---

## 0. Layout

```
safety_cot_heads/
├── configs/
│   ├── models.yaml             # model registry (Llama-2 / Mistral / judge)
│   ├── datasets.yaml           # dataset registry
│   └── experiments/
│       ├── exp01_reproduce_ships_sahara/
│       ├── exp02_judge_pipeline/
│       ├── exp03_safety_vs_random_ablation/
│       ├── exp04_coherency_head_discovery/
│       ├── exp05_joint_disentangled_ablation/
│       └── exp06_cot_trajectory_analysis/
├── data/raw/                   # vendored BeaverTails + SHA prompt files
├── scripts/                    # CLI entry points (run_attribution.py, …)
├── src/safety_cot_heads/
│   ├── attribution/            # ships, sahara, coherency, quality, random
│   ├── analysis/               # metrics, overlap, dose_response, trajectory, plots
│   ├── data/                   # beaver, jailbreakbench, maliciousinstruct, benign, …
│   ├── generation/             # prompts, decoding, generate
│   ├── interventions/          # ablation (hooks), surgery (in-place), patching
│   ├── judging/                # judge, prompts, parse, manual_validation
│   ├── models/                 # masks, custom_llama, custom_mistral, loading
│   ├── utils/                  # device, seed, io, logging
│   └── _legacy/                # verbatim upstream code (sha/ + cots/)
└── tests/                      # pytest (no GPU/model download required)
```

---

## 1. One-time setup

```bash
# 1. conda env
conda create -n safety_cot_heads python=3.11 -y
conda activate safety_cot_heads

# 2. install (editable) + deps
cd safety_cot_heads
pip install -e . -r requirements.txt

# 3. smoke-test the package
pytest -q tests/
python -c "from safety_cot_heads import attribution, generation, judging; print('ok')"
```

If the active conda env shows up as `(safety_cot_heads)` and `pytest` reports
all green (currently 19/19), you are good to go.

> **HF auth.**  Llama-2/3 are gated.  Run `huggingface-cli login` once with a
> token that has access, or set `HF_TOKEN` in the environment.  Set
> `HF_HOME=/path/with/space` if your `$HOME` is small.

> **Device override.**  All scripts honour `SAFETY_COT_DEVICE=cuda:1` /
> `cpu` / `mps`.  No code path hardcodes `cuda:0`.

---

## 2. Running the pipeline, one step at a time

Experiment run configs are grouped under `configs/experiments/exp*/` using the
same experiment numbering as `docs/ExperimentTracker.md`.  Every script accepts
`--config <path>`, optional `--overrides key=value ...` (OmegaConf dotlist), and
a `--dry-run` flag that loads the dataset & writes a plan json without touching
the model.

### Step 1 — Discover safety heads

```bash
# SHIPS — per-prompt → dataset ranking
python -m scripts.run_attribution \
    --config configs/experiments/exp01_reproduce_ships_sahara/01-ships-discovery.yaml

# Sahara — greedy SVD search
python -m scripts.run_attribution \
    --config configs/experiments/exp01_reproduce_ships_sahara/02-sahara-discovery.yaml
```

Outputs (per run):
* `runs/01-ships-discovery/ships.jsonl`               – per-prompt scores
* `runs/01-ships-discovery/ships_dataset_ranking.json` – consensus top-K
* `runs/02-sahara-discovery/sahara.json`              – ranked + step history

> Quick smoke without GPU/weights: append `--dry-run` to either command.

**Review point.** Open the `*_dataset_ranking.json` files — sanity-check that
top heads live in the expected mid layers, that all `(layer, head)` indices
are in range, and that the SHIPS prompt template renders correctly.

### Step 2 — Baseline + ablation generations on JailbreakBench

```bash
# 2a. Baseline (no mask)
python -m scripts.run_generation \
    --config configs/experiments/exp03_safety_vs_random_ablation/03-baseline.yaml

# 2b. Safety-head ablation (reads ranking from Step 1)
python -m scripts.run_generation \
    --config configs/experiments/exp03_safety_vs_random_ablation/04-safety-head-ablation.yaml

# 2c. Controls
python -m scripts.run_generation --config configs/experiments/exp03_safety_vs_random_ablation/05-random-head-ablation.yaml
python -m scripts.run_generation --config configs/experiments/exp03_safety_vs_random_ablation/06-layer-matched-random.yaml
```

Each writes `runs/<exp>/completions_<condition>.jsonl` with one row per
prompt: `id`, `prompt`, `rendered_prompt`, `completion`, `model`,
`condition`, `decoding`, `mask_cfg_active`, `timestamp`.

`scripts/run_ablation.py` is a thin alias to `run_generation` kept for
naming parity.

**Review point.** `head | tail -1 runs/04-*/completions_*.jsonl` — confirm
the completion text differs from the baseline for the same prompt id.

### Step 3 — Coherency + quality head discovery (the new modules)

```bash
python -m scripts.run_attribution --config configs/experiments/exp04_coherency_head_discovery/07-coherency-discovery.yaml
python -m scripts.run_attribution --config configs/experiments/exp05_joint_disentangled_ablation/08-quality-discovery.yaml
```

The coherency config selects the scoring mode via
`method_args.mode = nll | judge_coherence | pathology | hybrid`.

> Status note: the coherency and quality attribution modules exist, but
> `scripts/run_attribution.py` currently dispatches only `ships` and `sahara`.
> Wire `method == "coherency"` and `method == "quality"` before running these
> two discovery configs end to end.

### Step 4 — Ablate coherency / quality / overlap conditions

```bash
python -m scripts.run_generation --config configs/experiments/exp04_coherency_head_discovery/07b-coherency-ablation.yaml
python -m scripts.run_generation --config configs/experiments/exp05_joint_disentangled_ablation/08b-quality-ablation.yaml
# After running Step 5 once you’ll know which heads to fill in to:
python -m scripts.run_generation --config configs/experiments/exp05_joint_disentangled_ablation/09-safety-minus-coherency.yaml
python -m scripts.run_generation --config configs/experiments/exp05_joint_disentangled_ablation/10-overlap-only.yaml
```

For 09/10 you have to edit the `heads.heads:` list inline using the overlap
report produced in Step 6.  (Or pass `--overrides heads.heads='[{layer: 10,
head: 0}, ...]'`.)

### Step 5 — Judge all generations

```bash
# Per-condition; repeat for every completions_*.jsonl produced above
python -m scripts.run_judge \
    --config configs/experiments/exp02_judge_pipeline/judge.yaml \
    --completions runs/03-baseline/completions_baseline.jsonl \
    --out         runs/03-baseline/judge_baseline.jsonl

python -m scripts.run_judge \
    --config configs/experiments/exp02_judge_pipeline/judge.yaml \
    --completions runs/04-safety-head-ablation/completions_safety_head_ablation.jsonl \
    --out         runs/04-safety-head-ablation/judge_safety_head_ablation.jsonl
# … one per condition; same pattern as the file paths used in 00-analysis.yaml
```

Each writes:
* `judge_<condition>.jsonl` — per-row 5-label safety judgement (parsed +
  raw + per-attempt retries with rising temperature on parse failure).
* `judge_<condition>.summary.json` — per-condition harmful/refusal/reasoning
  rates and coverage.

### Step 6 — Cross-condition analysis

```bash
python -m scripts.run_analysis --config configs/experiments/exp05_joint_disentangled_ablation/00-analysis.yaml
```

Writes to `runs/analysis/`:
* `summary_by_condition.json` — every condition’s rates side by side.
* `overlap_report.json` — pairwise Jaccard + intersection sets for the
  named attribution rankings.
* `heatmap_<name>.png` — per-attribution `(layer × head)` score heatmap.

Use the intersection in `overlap_report.json` to fill `09-` and `10-`
experiment configs, then re-run Steps 4 and 5 for those two.

### (Optional) Step 7 — Sweep matrix

```bash
python -m scripts.make_experiment_matrix \
    --matrix configs/experiments/exp03_safety_vs_random_ablation/matrix.yaml \
    --out    runs/matrix/
# → runs/matrix/<condition>__<model>.yaml — one config per cell
# Feed each into run_generation:
for cfg in runs/matrix/*.yaml; do
    python -m scripts.run_generation --config "$cfg"
done
```

---

## 3. Useful flags

| Flag                              | Meaning                                                |
| --------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------ |
| `--dry-run`                       | load dataset + dump plan json, skip model              |
| `--overrides a.b=c d=e`           | OmegaConf dotlist overrides applied last               |
| `SAFETY_COT_DEVICE=cuda:1`        | force device used by `load_model` / `LoadedModel`      |
| `HF_HOME=/scratch/hf`             | redirect HF cache off `$HOME`                          |
| `HF_TOKEN=...`                    | gated-model auth                                       |

---

## 4. Tests

```bash
pytest -q tests/                # all 19 tests, no GPU, no network
```

* `test_masks.py` — `HeadMaskController` is identity at `scale=1.0` and
  zeroes the right head slice at `scale=0.0` (uses a stub Llama-shaped
  `nn.Module`, no downloads).
* `test_json_parsing.py` — judge parser handles clean / fenced / messy /
  garbage / spaced-key JSON.
* `test_head_selection.py` — `uniform_random` / `layer_matched` shapes,
  determinism, per-layer distribution preservation.
* `test_metrics.py` — Wilson CI edges, `harmful_rate` / `refusal_rate`,
  `aggregate_safety` per-condition counts.

---

## 5. Reproducing the upstream papers verbatim

The upstream scripts still work as-is from `_legacy/`:

```bash
python -m safety_cot_heads._legacy.sha.get_ships          # original SHIPS
python -m safety_cot_heads._legacy.sha.sahara_attribution # original Sahara
python -m safety_cot_heads._legacy.cots.judge_test_script # original CoT judge
```

The new modules in `attribution/`, `judging/`, `generation/` are drop-in
replacements built on top of them.

